I".<p>I’m going to show you how to make your GHCi prompt the Haskell logo.</p>

<h3 id="steps">Steps:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Firstly, install and select one of the many <a href="https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts">nerd fonts</a> as your terminal font.</li>
  <li>Now, edit your <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ghci.conf</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.ghci</code> file accordingly:
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>:set prompt "\ESC[94m\STX\ue61f  \ESC[m\STX"
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>And start up GHCi again… and there you go. Haskell logo as the prompt.</p>
